Commentary: A strong, gutsy leave from Latham. A good length ball pitching outside off. It comes in. Latham shoulders arms to it and the ball was inches away from hitting the off pole.
Full outside off. Latham has no problems leaving this alone as this was away from the stumps and shaping further away.
Another away swinger to the left-hander. It pitches outside off, Latham lets it carry to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Latham gets bat on ball for the first time as he defends this one.
Outside off and moving away. Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Slightly fuller outside off. Latham has nothing to do with it. Maiden to begin with.
Gabriel starts with a full ball outside off. Debutant Young keeps his nerves and leaves his first ball in international cricket alone.
Full and wide outside off. Asking Will Young to have a feel at that but he is happy to keep his calm and leave it alone.

NOT OUT! The pitching seemed to be an issue and it was the issue for West Indies. They lose one of their reviews very early on. Good length ball pitching outside off and it comes back in a lot. Young gets on his front foot and looks to defend but he misses and gets hit on the back pad. The West Indies players appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Shannon has a chat with his skipper and Holder backs his bowler and signals the 'T' Ultra Edge comes in and it detects no spike. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows that the ball is hitting the stumps but the impact is outside off. Young survives!
Outside off and shaping away. Young leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on the fourth stump line. Will is content to leave that.
Full around off. Young taps it to point but cannot get his first run in Test cricket.

New Zealand and Latham are up and running. Full around off, Latham leans on his drive and hits it through covers. The ball does not have the legs to get to the fence. The fielder cleans it up. Three taken.
Good ball! Length ball which is in the channel of uncertainty around off. Young looks to defend but the ball shapes away and goes past the outside edge of Young's willow.
On the pads, Young looks to flick but it goes off his thigh pad to fine leg and he takes a leg bye.
Length ball on off, Latham keeps it out.
Good length delivery just outside off. Latham shoulders arms to it.

Edged but falls short! Good ball from Roach. Good length ball on off. He tempts Latham to come forward, The Kiwi batter does. He closes the face of the bat towards mid on. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards gully. Brooks there dives forward half-heartedly but the ball falls short of him.
Young is up and running in Test cricket! Full around off, Young leans on his drive and places it through cover-point for a single.
FOUR! First one of the game and it comes from the bat of Latham. Full around off, Latham leans forward and creams his drive through point for a boundary.
Down the leg side, Latham leaves it.
Outside off, Latham leaves it alone. The ball keeps going away and Dowrich gets only a glove to it. Allowing the batters to take a bye.

EDGED AND FOUR! Right between the keeper and first slip. A brilliant delivery from Gabriel. It pitches on off and shapes away just a tad. Young looks to defend but the ball straightens and kisses the outside edge of his willow. It goes to the right of the keeper. Dowrich initially goes for it but then decides to leave for Bravo at first slip. He does not react and the ball goes to the third man fence.  First boundary for Will Young in international cricket. Not the way he would have liked but he will take it.

OUT! LBW! Young's debut does not last long. Shane Dowrich can breathe a sigh of relief. Excellent delivery and Gabriel's early effort has an early reward to show for it. A pacy ball which is full and comes back in sharply. Young looks to defend but his feet go nowhere. He misses it and gets hit on the pad. An appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. No waiting from Young as he knows he is dead in front. Young's debut does not last long and West Indies have an early breakthrough.

The umpires check to see if it was a bump ball. Replays show it is clean as a whistle.

Phenomenal man with yet another masterclass in batting. The New Zealand skipper gets to his milestone in style! Length ball wide outside off, Williamson punches it through cover-point and gets to his ton. His teammates all get on their feet and applaud their talismanic skipper. FOUR! DOUBLE HUNDRED FOR KANE WILLIAMSON! WOW! This man is a legend! What a fabulous knock this has been. It is not an easy pitch to bat on but Williamson has made it look like a walk in the park. Terrific from the New Zealand skipper who is once again leading from the front. Everyone on this ground is up on their feet applauding the genius of this  man. He gets to his milestone in style. Full outside off, Williamson leans forward and drives it exquisitely through covers to bring up his 3rd double century! Williamson hugs Mitchell and then removes his helmet and raises his bat and helmet to soak in all the applause. World Class!
FOUR! Action replay! Once again overpitched outside off, Williamson is quick to cream his drive through covers. Jeez! This man is a poetry in motion when he bats!

OUT! CAUGHT! Roach gets his 3rd and he deserves this. He has been the best bowler in this innings so far. Has gone past the edge a lot of time but finally gets that. FOUR! Gorgeous! This can be watched in loop a million times and it will just be as amazing as it was the first time. Full around off, Williamson gets on his front foot and drives it perfectly through mid on for a boundary. The toughest shot to play in cricket but this man makes it look like bread and butter.
SIX! That is hammered! Full ball on middle, Williamson lofts it over mid-wicket for a maximum.

OUT! CAUGHT! NO! IT IS A NO BALL! Kemar, Kemar, Kemar! What have you done? Willamson gets a lifeline and a big one. Roach has no one but himself to blame for this one. Good length ball pitching aorund off. Williamson goes for the big drive but gets a thick outside edge which goes straight into the mitts of Shamrah Brooks. The West Indies players celebrate but their celebration is cut short. The third umpire finds nothing behind the crease and signals it as no ball. A huge cheer from the crowd and the Kiwi skipper can continue his marathon innings.  When nothing goes your way, nothing does. That is what is happening to West Indies.

That went little too fine but Kane won't care as he gets to his highest score in Tests. What an innings, what a player and guess what, it will continue for now. 300 on mind?

OUT! CAUGHT! Kane departs but what an innings. Absolute gem of an innings from the Kiwi captain. He walks off to a standing ovation from the crowd and his teamamates in the dressing room. Williamson had to go after the bowling as New Zealand are eyeing quick runs before declaration. Jospeh runs in and bangs it short. Kane goes for the pull but fails to get the timing. It went straight down the throat of Chase at deep mid-wicket. He is not dropping it. End of a classy innings from Kane Williamson.

Length delivery outside off, Bravo lets it go.

OUT! TIMBER! Jamieson knocks over Bravo with a ripper! What a delivery from him. Top work and Jamieson strikes in his first over. The decent-looking stand has been broken. After bowling a couple of shortish length and hitting the gloves with a steep bounce, Jamieson bowls it fullish and around off, it comes back in as Bravo looks to flick but is beaten all ends up with this inswinger. He gets to hear his sticks rattled behind.

OUT! LBW! Yes, Chase has to go! Three reds it is. And with that half the Windies side is back in the hut now. Length ball around off and middle, Chase looks to defend off his back foot but misses to get hit on the pad. A loud, loud appeal but nothing from the umpire. Williamson has a word with the bowler and the keeper and he signals the 'T'. Let's see what the replays have got to show. Is there any bat? Ultra Edge confirms it is pad first. What does the Ball Tracker show? Pitching in line and hitting the stumps. Chase has to go. Excellent review from Williamson and New Zealand.
Good length delivery on middle, Holder looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Length ball outside off, Holder shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length on off, Holder keeps it out.
Length delivery on off, Holder blocks it off the back foot.
NO BALL! Wagner oversteps! Full delivery on off, Holder pushes it to point.

NO BALL! Wagner has pinned Holder right front of the wicket. He has been given out and he is walking off. But hello! Wagner has overstepped. Holder gets a reprieve.
Length ball around off, Holder pushes it towards the cover region for one.
FOUR! Whipped! A length ball around off, Blackwood drills it through mid on for a boundary.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid on and they take a quick single. Good running.
Shortish and around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket.

BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Holder looks to defend but misses it.
Back of a length delivery on off, Holder keeps it out.
Bouncer on off, Holder ducks under it.
Full on off, Blackwood plays it to point.
Good length delivery outside off, Blackwood offers no shot to this one.
Full on off, Blackwood drives it towards mid off for a single.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Holder looks to defend but misses it.

On a good length and outside off, Holder shoulders arms to this one.
Jamieson bowls a bouncer, Blackwood does well to duck under it.

Beaten! Just outside off on a good length, Holder feels for it and goes for the drive but misses.
This time he controls himself and allows the wide one to go to the keeper.
Boult goes fuller and just wide outside off, Holder covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
FOUR! Flicked nicely! Boult goes for the magic delivery and bowls it full on middle and leg, Holder flicks it superbly through mid-wicket for his first boundary.
Boult bowls the last ball of the over from wide of the crease and makes it to go away. Holder lets it be.

Good stop near the fence! Full ball on middle, Blackwood flicks it through mid-wicket. There is no one in the deep and the ball is racing away. However, the mid-wicket fielder gives it a chase and manages to flick the ball before the ropes with a dive. Fine save. Three taken. 100 up for West Indies.
Good length and around off, blocked.
In the channel outside off, Holder lets it be.
Fuller and around off, driven to the cover fielder.
Outside off, Jason allows it to go to the keeper.
FOUR! Fine shot to end the over! Short ball on the body. Not too pacy. Holder swivels and pulls it over mid-wicket. It goes to the fence.

FOUR! Short of a length delivery on leg, Holder looks to pull but gets a top edge. It goes over the keeper towards fine leg for a boundary.

Shortish and outside off, Blackwood punches it on the up but finds the point fielder. Wait, wait, says skipper Holder.
A bouncer and Blackwood goes for the pull but gets a top edge that goes over the keeper. Short third man gets around. A single taken.
Wagner goes for the slower fuller ball but it goes down the leg side. Holder looks to flick but it is well down the leg side for him to make any connection. With that, it is LUNCH on Day 3.
Full ball down the leg side to begin the session. Blackwood looks to flick but misses.
Full and on middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Bouncer now! It is just outside off. Blackwood sways away.
Good length and around middle, Blackwood looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pad.
Outside off, Blackwood lets it be.
Goes full but way outside off. An easy leave for the batter. Maiden to begin from Boult.
Length delivery outside off, Holder leaves it alone.
Back of a length on off, Holder defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Holder looks to defend but misses it.
Length ball on off, Holder blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Southee strikes! He doesn't take long. Blackwood is known for playing his shots and he has been out in the middle for a decent time now. He doesn't want to miss out on the scoring opportunities. Southee lures him with a fuller one which is wide outside off. Blackwood throws the willow as he tries to drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge. Latham at second slip makes no mistake.
Back of a length outside off, Joseph lets it go.
Full and outside off, Alzarri leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT! Southee gets his 4th and Joseph departs without troubling the scorers. Southee goes wide of the crease and bowls it full and just outside off, Joseph looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge The ball goes low to Mitchell who takes a very sharp catch at third slip. A double wicket maiden from Southee.
Back of a length on off, Holder looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes towards the slip region where it falls short of the fielder.
Short delivery outside off, Holder looks to pull but misses it.
Full on middle, Holder flicks it through square leg for a single.
Length delivery on middle, Roach defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, Roach leaves it alone.

In the air but away from the fielder. Short ball outside off, Holder looks to hammer it over the leg side but he mistimes it. Luckily for him, it goes over the man at mid on who chases the ball and keeps it down to 2.
Good length delivery outside off, Holder leaves it alone.
Full on off, Holder drives it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it just before the ropes. The batsmen get two runs.
Outside off, Jason offers no shot to this one.
Short delivery on middle, Holder pulls it through square leg for a single to keep the strike for the next over.
Back of a length on middle, Holder keeps it out.

Full delivery on off, Holder keeps it out.

OUT! TIMBER! Full, and fast and he goes through the defense of Roach. A beauty from Jamieson. A length ball around off, angled on. Roach looks to defend but the ball goes through and disturbs the woodwork behind. He was stuck in his crease there.
Length delivery outside off, Gabriel offers no shot to this one.
Back of a length on off, Gabriel defends it off the back foot.
Length ball on off, Gabriel keeps it out.
There's the bumper! It is right on middle but Shannon does well to sit under it.

WOW! What a nasty delivery. That took off after pitching. Shortish and outside off, Gabriel gets away from the firing line but that is not done. It took off and Blundell had to leap high in the air to collect the ball.
Full on middle, Holder flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.

Swing and a miss! Gabriel clears his intention. He is not there to just block the balls. Goes for the mighty swing but misses. Had he connected, the ball would've landed somewhere in West Indies. Smile from the skipper from the other end.
Good length delivery on off, Gabriel looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Full on middle, Gabriel flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.

DROPPED! Short of a length delivery, Holder looks to pull but gets a top edge. It goes towards square leg where substitute Mitchell Santner tries to take the catch but spills it. The batsmen cross ends.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting the wicket. Wagner gets his second wicket. After bowling a bumper he goes for the fuller one to Gabriel. He looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. An appeal and the finger is raised. Gabriel refers it upstairs but it won't help as there is no bat which is confirmed by the Ultra Edge. And the Ball Tracker shows that it will be umpire's call on hitting the wicket.
Southee is right on the money! A length ball outside off, this one comes back in but Brathwaite covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper. Good leave in the end.
Goes full and around middle, Brathwaite flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Brathwaite is up and running with a couple. Southee dishes it full and on the pads, Brathwaite flicks it wide of the fine leg fielder and gets two.
Good length and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Full again but this one is outside off, Brathwaite drives it towards the cover fielder.
Around off on a length, defended back to the bowler. Quality first over but equally well negotiated by Brathwaite.
Good length and outside off, Campbell lets it be.
Campbell is off the mark! Boult goes full and outside off, Campbell looks to drive but a thick outside edge is induced. Luckily for him it goes through the gap between gully and point. Two taken.

OUT! CAUGHT! Yes! There is no conclusive evidence for the third umpire to overturn the onfield call. Looked touch and go. An absolute ripper of a delivery from Boult. He pitches it just outside off, Campbell is squared up as he looks to defend with hard hands. The induced outside edge goes to the second slip fielder. Latham catches it really low and New Zealand celebrate. Campbell is not going anywhere. The two umpires get together and refer it upstairs. The soft signal is out. That is going to play a big role. Let's see what the replays show. It looks really inconclusive there. With one angle it looks like the fingers are under the ball while another one suggests that it might have kissed the turf. Tough decision to make and the third umpire goes with the onfield call. Campbell has to go. New Zealand have struck early in this innings.
Back of a length on off, Bravo defends it off the back foot.

Outside off, Kraigg shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Brathwaite offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Bravo defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! SHOT! That is classy cover drive! One of the best shots in match. Full and wide outside off, Bravo leans into the shot and strokes it through the covers. Holds the pose for the cameras there!
FOUR! Have some of that now. Bravo, you beauty. Overpitched again and outside off as well. Bravo hammers it over extra cover for a boundary. Intent from Darren.
Back of a length outside off, Bravo offers no shot to this one.
Bouncer on middle, Bravo ducks under it.
Good length delivery outside off, Bravo offers no shot to this one.
Length ball on middle, Brathwaite flicks it through square leg for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Wagner strikes on the second ball of his spell and it is the massive wicket of Bravo. A couple of good shots and he is dismissed. Wagner is fired up. Good length and outside off, Bravo pokes at it without moving his feet. The outside edge goes to the left of Southee at second slip. He tumbles to that side and takes a fine catch.
Full and outside off, Brooks leaves it alone.
Brooks is off the mark with a fine flick. Full ball on middle, he flicks it through square leg. The fine leg fielder comes around but by the time he returns the ball to the keeper, two taken.
Bouncer on middle, Brooks ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one goes. Wagner gets second wicket in the over. He is delighted. Brooks fails again. A length ball on the pads, Brooks goes for the flick again. This time he hits it uppishly and there is a fielder at square leg. Conway, the substitute, there makes no mistake.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another one bites the dust and it is Southee who gets a wicket now. Poor, poor stuff from Brathwaite. Short and wide outside off, Brathwaite looks to upper cut but gets a faint edge to the keeper. Blundell makes no mistake. New Zealand are on fire here.
Full and wide outside off, driven well but straight to the cover fielder.
Full on middle, Blackwood drives it to mid on.
Southee bowls a bumper, Blackwood ducks under it.
Full on middle, Blackwood flicks it through square leg for a single.

Full on middle, Blackwood flicks it to mid-wicket.

Full on off, Blackwood drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Back of a length on off, Blackwood taps it to point.
Outside off, Jermaine offers no shot to this one.
A good length ball outside off to begin, Chase shoulders arms.
Outside off, left alone.
Misses the line and bowls the full ball down the leg side. Chase looks to flick but misses.
Shortish and around off, this one comes back on. Chase does well to work it around the corner.
Lovely delivery! The last one came back in and this one goes other way after pitching. Chase looks to defend but misses.
This one keeps low. But Chase does well to bring his bat down in time to defend. A maiden to begin the final session on Day 3.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
NO BALL! Wagner oversteps! Length delivery on middle, Blackwood keeps it out.
FOUR! Good shot! Full on middle, Blackwood lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
Length delivery on off, Blackwood punches it towards covers for a single.
Back of a length on off, Chase looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes past second slip towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
Bouncer from Wagner, Chase does well to duck under it.
FOUR! Nice shot! Length ball on middle, Chase flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Back of a length on off, Blackwood defends it off the back foot.
WIDE! Length delivery wide outside off, Blackwood lets it go.
Good length ball on off, Blackwood pushes it to covers.
Full on middle, Blackwood flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Terrific shot! Full on off, Blackwood drives it through mid off for a boundary.
Bouncer on middle, Blackwood ducks under it.
Bumper again from Wagner, Blackwood does well to duck under it.
Bouncer from Wagner, Blackwood sits under it.

Short delivery on off, Blackwood looks to play an upper cut but misses it. It goes towards the keeper where Blundell appeals for caught behind and the umpire raises his finger. Blackwood reviews it! Ultra Edge shows there is a flat line when the ball passes the bat. The decision is overturned and Blackwood survives.
Short and outside off, Jermaine ducks under it.
Fuller and around off, blocked.
Length ball around off, kept out by Chase.
FIVE WIDES! Jamieson goes short but it goes well over the batsman and the leaping keeper. Wided and it races away to the fence too.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards the off side.
Length ball around off, Chase flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Good length and around off, Chase is solid in defense again.

OUT! LBW! Yes, there is no bat and it is hitting the wicket too. Chase has been removed with an absolute ripper of a delivery from Jamieson. It is the inswinging yorker from him and Chase is all over the place as he tries to keep it out. He misses to get hit on the pad. A loud appeal follows and the umpire agrees. Chase opts to challenge the onfield call. But it won't really help him because Ultra Edge shows no bat and the Ball Tracker shows it to be crashing on the middle pole. Chase has to go.
Back of a length and just outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder.
Short again, pushed towards mid on this time.
Bouncer but this one is down the leg side. Blackwood lets it be.
Good stop! Shortish and around middle, Blackwood pushes it to the right of the bowler. Wagner dives that side and pushes it towards mid-wicket.
SIX! BOOM! Enough of your short stuff says Blackwood and takes Wagner on. Short and around off and middle, Blackwood swivels and hammers it way over the deep square leg fence. That went way back.
Short again, this time he nudges it down to fine leg for one.

EDGED BUT DROPPED! Short and wide outside off, Blackwood throws the willow at it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes high over Taylor at first slip. He leaps high and gets hands to it but the rebound drops away from him. Good effort.
Back of a length on off, Holder defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Holder keeps it out.
Full and outside off, Holder offers no shot to this one.
Length ball outside off, Holder shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Good shot! Length delivery on middle, Holder flicks it towards fine leg for a boundary.
Back of a length on off, Blackwood pushes it to covers.
FOUR! That is put away! Short ball on middle, Blackwood pulls it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Short and just outside off, Blackwood sways away from the line.
Short ball on middle, it is pushed back to the bowler. Wagner quickly picks the ball and threatens to throw the ball at the stumps.
Back of a length and on middle, Blackwood hops and keeps it out.
FOUR! Short again and Blackwood hammers it. He is not going to bog down to this short stuff. He swivels and slams it over mid-wicket and it races away to the fence.
In the channel outside off, Holder shoulders arms.
Beauty! Just outside off and on a good length, Holder pokes at it to get beaten. He played for the away swing but it went straight.
This time he covers his sticks and offers no shot.
Goes to play this time as Jamieson pitches it fuller and around off, but this one moves away sharply to beat the outside edge.
Dropped! Full and wide outside off, Holder goes for the drive but ends up hitting it uppishly towards point fielder. Young there dives to his left, gets both the hands but spills it in the end.

Another one goes down! This time it is Blundell who puts it down. A length ball angled in. Holder looks to defend but the ball comes back in sharply. It takes the inside edge and goes to the left of the keeper. Blundell moves to that side and gets his gloves to it but it doesn't stick. Two drops in two balls. The batsmen get two runs.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the off side.
Full again, Blackwood drives it towards cover.
Length ball around middle, pushed towards mid on for nothing.
Short this time, Blackwood forces it back to the bowler.
Length ball around off, poked towards the on side.

EDGY! Length ball just outside off, Blackwood looks to defend but is squared up. The outside edge goes past the diving gully fielder. Before one of the fielder can do the mop up work, they take three.

EDGED AND FOUR! Blackwood is going after the wide ones right now. Full and wide outside off, Jermaine throws his bat at it as he looks to drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge that goes well over the leaping slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length ball on middle and leg, Blackwood defends it out.
Good length and around off, this one rises awkwardly. Blackwood does well to defend it out.
Short and on middle, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Goes slightly full. Blackwood works it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Up and over! Blackwood is playing a little gem of an innings here. Short and wide outside off, he slashes it over backward point and it races away to the fence. He moves to 40 in just 48 balls.
Fuller and around off, defended towards mid off.

NO BALL!  Holder is caught at covers. Holder is shocked! He is not sure what he has done here. A soft dismissal. Mitchell is delighted. Full ball outside off, Holder drills the drive but straight to the cover fielder. Mitchell Santner, the substitute makes no mistake. But hang on. Mitchell has overstepped. And he will have to wait for his maiden Test wicket.
Length ball around middle, it is clipped through square leg for a couple.

OUT! LBW! Yes, Mitchell has got his man. He has his maiden Test wicket. Poor, poor batting from him. He got a life just 1 ball ago. He played a reckless shot then and he tried something similar but this time he has to go. Fuller and around off and middle, Holder looks to slog it on the leg side via a flick but he misses it completely. He is struck on the pads. A massive appeal and the finger goes up. Holder asks for the review straightaway but that looked out to the naked eye. Let's see what the replays have got to show. No bat involved, Ultra Edge confirms. The Ball Tracker shows it to be clipping the leg pole. Holder has to go and Mitchell and the Kiwis celebrate.
Full and wide outside off, Joseph shoulders arms.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Alzarri.
Full and swinging in but it is wide outside off so Joseph lets it be. End of a successful over form Mitchell.
Good length and on middle and leg, Blackwood looks to work it on the leg side but gets an inside edge on the pad.

In the air... safe! That went miles in the air but Jamieson failed to get there. A length ball outside off, Blackwood looks to hammer it over the bowler's head but miscues it high in the air. Jamieson from mid on runs back and tries to catch but he fails to get there. Two taken.
Bouncer and on middle, Blackwood sits under it.

In the air... safe! Chance for a run out. Missed. Who missed? Well, Kane Williamson. Probably for the first time he has done something and it has not gone his way. Fuller and outside off, Blackwood looks to hammer it over mid off but once again it goes off the toe end. It falls well short of Williamson. But West Indies want to get it done quickly it seems as they go for the risky single. Williamson collects the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses. Blackwood made a big dive but had Williamson hit, he would've been short.
Very full and outside off, Joseph squeezes it out towards backward point.
Good length and outside off, left alone.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Sharp bouncer around off, Blackwood does well to get away from the firing line.
Good drive but for no run. Full and wide outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Around off on a length, pushed back to the bowler.
Back of a length on off, Blackwood pushes it to mid off.
Short delivery on off, Blackwood looks to cut but gets an outside edge. It goes towards first slip on one bounce. The fielder misfields and concedes a single.
Bouncer down the leg side. Blackwood ducks.
Short ball on middle, Blackwood hops and works it to fine leg for one.
Around off on a length, Joseph is solid in defense.
Bouncer on middle, Alzarri ducks under it.
Fuller and on middle, Joseph flicks it well but Jamieson moves to his right swiftly to stop the ball.
Play and a miss! Joseph is lured into the drive as he plays it away from his body. Beaten.
Back of a length and around off, punched towards the short cover fielder.
Short and wide outside off, Blackwood cuts it through cover-point. The third man fielder runs to his right and stops the ball but Blackwood gets three.

EDGY! A length ball around off, Joseph looks to defend but gets an inside edge on the pad. The ball goes past the sticks and runs to the fence at fine leg. But Jamieson, the big man, runs to his left towards fine leg and makes a diving stop. Saves two for the side. Excellent commitment.
Full and wide outside off, Joseph lifts it over cover-point and gets a brace.
A solid front foot defense from him this time.
Bangs it short and shows some aggression. Joseph ducks under it. Wagner keeps staring at him as he goes past the umpire.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR BLACKWOOD! He is the only positive for the Windies with the bat. He has done really well for these runs. Got himself in and then took the bowlers on. A short ball on the body, he clips it fine. The fine leg fielder runs to his right, dives and tries to pull the ball back in play but fails to do so. Blackwood raises his bat to his teammates.
On the pads again, it is worked towards fine leg for one.
FOUR! Clipped through square leg from Joseph. Full ball on the pads, Joseph uses his wrists and flicks it through square leg and bags himself a boundary.
Beaten! Short and just around off, shapes away as Joseph pokes at it.
Shortish and on middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! DRILLED THROUGH THE COVERS! That is some shot from Joseph. A low full toss around off, he creams the drive through the covers. Classic cover drive. 13 from the over.
Bouncer on middle, Blackwood ducks under it.
Outside off on a length. An easy leave for Blackwood.
Length ball around off, pushed to the left of the bowler. The ball goes to the right of mid off and they sneak a single.
Full and wide outside off, Joseph looks to go big but ends up slicing it over gully. Two taken.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and wide outside off, Joseph drives it towards mid off uppishly. It bounces short of Williamson. A single taken.
Full and on the pads, clipped to fine leg for an easy single.
Full and outside off, Joseph looks to drive but it takes the inner half and goes to deep mid-wicket. Before the fielder from the ring can get to the ball, three more for Joseph.
Short on middle, tucked away on the leg side for one.

FOUR! SLAMMED AWAY! This is good batting from Joseph here. He is enjoying the batting it seems. Full and wide outside off, he takes a long stride forward and drills the drive through backward point. It races away to the fence. Shake of the head from Southee.
Classy drive but for no run. Southee overpitches and Jospeh drives it well but finds mid off.

Terrific save from Wagner at the fine leg fence. A length ball on the pads, Joseph looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. A stifled appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire. The ball is racing away to the fence but Wagner from fine leg gets to the ball with a dive and keeps it into the play. Two leg byes taken.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Short and outside off, punched on the up to sweeper cover for one.

FOUR! Easy pickings for Alzarri. Wagner runs in and tries to bowl the yorker but ends up bowling a high full toss. Joseph helps it on its way to the deep mid-wicket fence via a well-timed flick. He moves to 25 in just 26 balls.
Good length and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Joseph ducks under it.
Fuller and around off, blocked towards cover for nothing.
Full and wide outside off, driven to the left of the mid off fielder for a single.
Short ball on middle, Alzarri ducks under it easily.
Fullish and on off, Joseph is solid in defense.

FOUR! It was in the air but wide of the third man fielder. Full and wide outside off, Joseph goes for the drive but ends up slicing it towards third man. Young there runs to his left and dives to catch. He gets fingertips to it but fails to hold on. That will go down as a drop but it was a very tough chance. Four more for Joseph by the way.
Length ball around middle, pushed towards mid on uppishly.
Fuller and around middle, pushed towards mid on again.
Short and around off, punched to mid off.
A single and it brings up 50-run stand between the two, in just 59 balls. Good length and around middle, it is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Bumper on middle, Joseph ducks.

Put down? Is it? Don't tell me. Yes, another one goes down but this was hit with brutal force from Joseph. Full ball outside off, he drills it. The ball goes quickly to Latham at covers. He kind of goes for the evasive action instead of trying to catch. Gets both hands but fails to hold on.
FOUR! Flicked. What a shot that is. Full ball on the pads, Joseph flicks it through square leg and bags a boundary.
Length ball around off, a solid front foot defense from Joseph.
SIX! Up and over! Runs coming thick and fast for West Indies. Short and wide outside off, Blackwood uppercuts it and it sails over the fence.

Appeal for LBW but turned down. Length ball on the pads, Jermaine looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes to the leg side and they sneak a leg bye. 150 up for West Indies.
Around off on a good length, pushed towards the off side for a quick single.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and wide outside off, driven to deep point for one.
Southee goes for the yorker. Joseph manages to flick it down to deep mid-wicket for one.
Length delivery on off, Joseph punches it through covers. The batsmen get three runs.
Full on middle, Blackwood flicks it through square leg for a single.
Back of a length outside off, Joseph offers no shot to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Joseph offers a solid defense on this one.
Full and outside off, Joseph lofts it over point for a couple.

FOUR! NAILED! What a shot! Joseph is telling his teammates how to do it. Full and wide outside off, Joseph creams it through the covers and it races away to the fence.
FOUR LEG BYES! Full on the pads, Joseph looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards fine leg for a boundary.
Length delivery outside off, Blackwood leaves it alone.
Back of a length outside off, Jermaine offers no shot to this one.
Full on middle, Blackwood flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
SIX! FIFTY FOR JOSEPH! What a way to get to the maiden half ton in Test match cricket. Brilliant ball striking. Short ball on middle, he swivels and hammers it over the fence at deep square leg.
FOUR! Short delivery on middle, Joseph looks to pull but gets a top edge. It goes towards fine leg for a boundary.

EDGY FOUR! And brings up 100-run stand between the two. What a stand this is turning out to be for the Windies. Full and wide outside off, Blackwood throws the bat at it. He gets a thick outside edge that flies over the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
BEATEN! Length delivery outside off, Blackwood looks to drive but misses it.

PUT DOWN! That is a regulation catch for Taylor but he spills it. Fuller and around off, it shapes away. Blackwood looks to drive but it goes off the outside edge and straight to first slip who drops it. New Zealand’s frustration continues.

100 for Jermaine Blackwood! This has been a fantastic knock from him under pressure! Full on middle, Blackwood flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.

Wagner bowls a short of a length delivery on leg, Joseph fends it uppishly towards square leg for a single.

DROPPED! Williamson is the culprit! Full on off, Joseph lofts it over mid off but does not get the timing on it. It goes towards the fielder where Williamson runs and tries to take it but fails to hold on. The batsmen get two runs.

OUT! CAUGHT! The partnership is finally broken. Joseph is a goner. Would have loved to see him get a ton here though, he has batted brilliantly. End of a very fluent knock by the pacer. Full delivery on off, Joseph lofts it over point but does not get the timing on it. It goes towards the fielder where substitute Mitchell Santner takes a good catch.
Length delivery on off, Blackwood punches it through point for a couple.
Full on middle, Blackwood punches it through mid on for a single.
Full and outside off, Roach looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third slip where it falls short of Southee.
Outside off, Roach leaves it alone.

OUT! Gone! Blackwood departs after a superb ton. New Zealand’s frustration finally comes to an end. Wagner is the man who has done the job. Can they now take the remaining wickets quickly? Short delivery on leg, Blackwood looks to pull but gets it off the glove. It goes towards square leg where Southee takes a comfortable catch.
Full on middle, Gabriel flicks it to mid-wicket.
Bouncer on middle, Gabriel ducks under it.
Length ball on middle, Gabriel looks to pull but gets it off the pads. It goes towards the leg side.
OUT! BOWLED! Full on middle, Gabriel looks to swing at it but misses it and gets bowled. Wagner gets his fourth wicket! NEW ZEALAND WIN BY AN INNINGS AND 134 RUNS!
